Uses of Package
org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml

  • Packages that use org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml 
    Package Description
    org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml  
  • Classes in org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml used by org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml 
    Class and Description
    Database
    A database element contains all genes from a single database/source.
    Gene
    The gene element represents a single gene, protein or transcript.
    GeneRef
    The geneRef element is a link to the gene definition under the species element.
    Genes
    A gene element represents a list of genes.
    Group
    A group of genes or nested groups.
    Groups
    Represents the list of ortholog groups.
    Notes
    The notes element is a special element, which allows adding information that is not general enough to be part of the standard.
    OrthoXML
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Property
    Key-value pair for group annotations, for instance statistics about the group members.
    Score
    The score element gives the value of a score and links it to the scoreDef element, which defines the score.
    ScoreDef
    The scoreDef element defines a score.
    Scores
    A list of score definitions.
    Species
    The species element contains all sequences of one species.
